The paper deals with managing null entries in pairwise comparisons matrices, which is a common problem in decision-making and optimization problems. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data science (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the mathematical foundations of pairwise comparisons and their application to decision-making, it is most likely to be classified under the sub-category of Mathematical Software (cs.MS).
